# Core Engineering Rules

- Keep changes small, reversible, and focused on one concern.
- Preserve runtime configuration behavior (`.env` baseline + runtime overrides).
- Do not hardcode provider/model values in feature logic.
- For backend route changes, verify payload validation and clear error details.
- For frontend actions, always include loading, success, and error states.
- Prefer explicit naming for buttons and user actions.
- Update docs when architecture or developer workflow changes.
- Run local quality checks before considering work complete.
